comment.name: Sample_description
comment.value: The seeds were stratified at 4C for 48 hours in darkness.  Seeds were rinsed in 100% ethanol and sterilized in 2.5% (v/v) sodium hypochlorite solution for 7 min, then washed with sterilized distilled water 3 times.  150-200 Seeds were plated in 10 clusters (app 20 seeds per cluster) on 1/2 MS 0.8% agar plates.  Seedlings were grown in 12 h light/12 h dark (12L:12D) for 11 days at constant 19C. The light source for germination and growth was cool-white fluorescent light at 70 umol/m2/s. On the 12th day the seedlings were transferred to continuous white light conditions at 100 umol/m2/s. Autoclaved.  20 seedlings clumped together. 19 C average, 19 C day, 19 C night. 50 % average, 50 % day, 50 % night. Murashige & Skoog basal salt mixture. Constant light.

Seeds were rinsed in 100% ethanol and sterilized in 2.5% (v/v) sodium hypochlorite solution for 7 min, then washed with sterilized distilled water 3 times.  70-100 Seeds were plated in 10 clusters (app 10 seeds per cluster) on 1/2 MS 0.8% agar plates. Seedlings were grown in 12 h light/12 h dark (12L:12D) for 11 days at constant 19C. The light source for germination and growth was cool-white fluorescent light at 70 umol/m2/s. On the 12th day the seedlings were transferred to continuous white light conditions at 100 umol/m2/s.  10-20 seeds clumped together. 19 C average, 19 C day, 19 C night. 50 % average, 50 % day, 50 % night. Murashige & Skoog basal salt mixture. 12 hour days, 12 hour nights.
